    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Jamesport Meeting House, built in 1731, is the oldest operating church building in Suffolk County.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamesport%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "James Tuthill founded the town in the early 1800s, naming it Jamesport and building a dock on Peconic Bay.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.eastlongisland.com/jamesport/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Jamesport once aimed to be a shipping port, but shallow waters at low tide prevented large ships from docking.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12,
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamesport%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Long Island Rail Road linked Jamesport to New York City, turning it into a resort area with bayfront hotels until 1952.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
